http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Govt.-releases-compensation-for-farmers/article14009323.ece

The State government has released Rs. 48.95 crore to provide ‘input subsidy’ to farmers who suffered crop loss due to drought in 2015-16. Growers of both agriculture and horticulture crops will get around Rs. 6,800 a hectare as compensation. Deputy Commissioner Umesh H. Kusugal told presspersons here on Tuesday that the amount would be transferred to bank accounts of small farmers. “ The district administration had sent a proposal of Rs. 82 crore as compensation,” he said.The input subsidy applies to horticulture crops grown in 13,869 ha and agriculture crops in 1,08,305 ha.